## Example 2 — Two-Column Proof Using ASA

**Given:** \(\angle L \cong \angle N\), \(\overline{LM} \cong \overline{NM}\), and \(M\) is between \(L\) and \(P\) and between \(N\) and \(Q\) such that \(\angle LMP\) and \(\angle NMQ\) are right angles.

**Prove:** \(\overline{LP} \cong \overline{NQ}\).

### Step 1: Identify the Strategy

We have two angles and the side between them. Prove △LMP ≅ △NMQ by ASA, then use CPCTC.

### Step 2: Two-Column Proof

| Statement | Reason |
|-----------|--------|
| 1. \(\angle L \cong \angle N\) | 1. Given |
| 2. \(\overline{LM} \cong \overline{NM}\) | 2. Given |
| 3. \(\angle LMP\) and \(\angle NMQ\) are right angles | 3. Given |
| 4. \(\angle LMP \cong \angle NMQ\) | 4. All right angles are congruent |
| 5. △LMP ≅ △NMQ | 5. ASA (steps 1, 2, 4) |
| 6. \(\overline{LP} \cong \overline{NQ}\) | 6. CPCTC |

### Step 3: Interpretation

The included side LM ≅ NM sits between the congruent angles ∠L ≅ ∠N and ∠LMP ≅ ∠NMQ, satisfying ASA.

✅ Answer: \(\overline{LP} \cong \overline{NQ}\) proved by ASA and CPCTC.

